
# PRD for ResumeCraft - Professional Resume Builder

## 1. Overview
ResumeCraft is an elegant personal resume webpage builder designed to help professionals showcase their skills, experience, and achievements in a visually appealing digital format.

## 2. Product Objectives
- Create a responsive, single-page resume website
- Provide elegant templates for different professional domains
- Enable easy customization without coding
- Optimize for both desktop and mobile viewing
- Support PDF export functionality

## 3. User Personas
**Primary User:** Job-seeking professionals (entry-level to executive)
**Secondary Users:** Freelancers, students, career changers

## 4. Core Features

### 4.1 Template Selection
- 5+ professionally designed templates
- Industry-specific designs (tech, creative, corporate, etc.)
- Live preview functionality

### 4.2 Content Sections
1. **Header Section**
   - Professional photo upload
   - Name with typography options
   - Contact information (email, phone, LinkedIn, etc.)
   - Professional tagline

2. **Summary Section**
   - Rich text editor
   - Character limit: 300 words

3. **Experience Section**
   - Timeline format
   - Company name, position, duration
   - Bullet point achievements (max 5 per position)
   - Skill tags for each role

4. **Education Section**
   - Degree, institution, year
   - GPA/achievements toggle
   - Relevant coursework

5. **Skills Section**
   - Skill categorization (technical, soft skills, languages)
   - Proficiency indicators (stars, bars, or percentages)
   - Skill tagging system

6. **Projects/Portfolio Section**
   - Project cards with images
   - Links to live projects/repositories
   - Tech stack tags

7. **Additional Sections (Optional)**
   - Certifications
   - Publications
   - Volunteer Work
   - Awards

### 4.3 Customization Options
- Color palette selector
- Font pairing options
- Layout variations (single column, split view)
- Section ordering
- Light/dark mode toggle

### 4.4 Export & Sharing
- PDF generation
- Unique URL for sharing
- Social media sharing buttons
- QR code generator for printed materials

## 5. Technical Requirements

### 5.1 Frontend
- React.js framework
- Responsive CSS with mobile-first approach
- PDF.js for export functionality
- Local storage for draft saving

### 5.2 Backend (Optional for V2)
- User accounts
- Cloud storage for resumes
- Multi-resume management
- Analytics dashboard

## 6. User Flow
1. Select template → 2. Fill sections → 3. Customize design → 4. Preview → 5. Export/Share

## 7. Success Metrics
- Time to complete first resume (<15 minutes)
- Mobile/desktop usage ratio
- Export conversion rate
- Average sections completed per resume

## 8. Future Enhancements
- AI-powered content suggestions
- Resume ATS optimization checker
- Cover letter generator
- Interview preparation module
- Integration with job boards

## 9. Accessibility Requirements
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Screen reader compatibility
- Keyboard navigation
- Color contrast validation

## 10. Security Considerations
- Client-side processing for privacy
- Optional encryption for saved resumes
- GDPR-compliant data handling

## 11. Performance Targets
- Page load time < 2s
- PDF generation < 5s
- Mobile performance score > 80 (Lighthouse)

## 12. Localization Support
- Multi-language templates
- Right-to-left language support
- Localized date/address formats
